Rapid testing centers have helped South Korea organize one of the fastest and most extensive testing procedures than any other country. On March 2, in Germany, the National Association of Compulsory Medical Insurance Physicians said it was willing to conduct about 12,000 tests a day on an outpatient basis, and a week earlier they could only do 10,700 tests a week.
