Quarantine measures for individuals whose tests tested positive for SARS-CoV-2, as well as monitoring people with whom such patients were in contact, had positive results.
Researchers working in the Italian city of Vaud, where a person died of COVID-19 for the first time in Italy, conducted two cycles of testing the entire population of about 3,400 people, with an interval of about ten days.
